      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Current battery level",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 29,
          "startingLine": 5848
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "%@ percent",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 29,
          "startingLine": 5849
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "%@%%",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 5738
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "About the app",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6884
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Mini Range is a simple range and charging companion for the Mini Cooper SE.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6866
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "The app estimates remaining range and charging needs based on battery level, driving conditions, temperature, speed, road surface, wind, tyres, and your own driving history if calibration is enabled.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6867
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "The estimates are designed to be practical rather than exact. The goal is to support everyday driving and simpler trip planning while maintaining a comfortable safety margin.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6868
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Mini Range was originally developed for the MINI Cooper SE 2019–2023, with calculations and defaults shaped around that car's battery size, range and real-world consumption.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6869
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "You can also use the app with other electric vehicles by creating a custom vehicle profile. For other vehicles, estimates should be treated as approximate, especially before calibration.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6870
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "If you log real trips, Mini Range can adjust estimates to your vehicle and driving patterns. Calibration becomes active after at least three logged trips for a driving mode.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6871
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "The main range view shows estimated remaining range, expected consumption, and an approximate distance between charging stops.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6872
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "The Trip tab helps estimate arrival battery level, charging time, and whether charging may be needed during longer drives. It accepts destinations, addresses, place names, and simple trip descriptions.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6873
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Charging plans are intended as a practical approximation. The app estimates when charging may be needed, but does not select or optimise specific charging locations. Always check charger availability and plan charging stops accordingly.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6874
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "The app is intentionally simpler than full route planners and is designed for quick, understandable estimates.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6875
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "You can optionally log trips to help the app calibrate to your own vehicle and driving conditions. All data stays on your device.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6876
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Real-world consumption always varies with weather, traffic, elevation, battery temperature, driving style, tyre pressure, and road conditions. Always use your own judgment and maintain a safe battery reserve.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 6877
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Done",
        "location": {
